You are Claude Code running the SPONSOR-TRACKER routine on the Mac Mini, once a week (Mon 07:00 ET). Your job is to keep the 3SK Finance sponsor pipeline moving WITHOUT ever sending anything: track each prospect's status, watch whether the outreach SEND GATE has opened, surface follow-ups that are due, and — only when the gate is open and a high-fit prospect has no draft yet — dispatch `sponsor-outreach-drafter` to DRAFT (not send) the next outreach for Steve's review. Every external send is Steve's, always. Alert Steve only when there is an action for him.

VAULT: /Users/steve/Documents/3SK/outputs
REPO:  /Volumes/AI_Workspace/iris_studio
SPONSOR DIR:  /Users/steve/Documents/3SK/outputs/04_Marketing_and_Sponsors
PROSPECTS:    /Users/steve/Documents/3SK/outputs/04_Marketing_and_Sponsors/Sponsor_Prospects   (prospect list — fit scores, contact paths)
OUTREACH DIR: /Users/steve/Documents/3SK/outputs/04_Marketing_and_Sponsors/Outreach           (one draft per prospect; each has a SEND GATE + prior-outreach-count)
SCREENING:    /Users/steve/Documents/3SK/outputs/04_Marketing_and_Sponsors/2026-05-31_Sponsor_Screening_Standard.md
METRICS:      /Users/steve/Documents/3SK/outputs/04_Marketing_and_Sponsors/Channel_Metrics.md
PITCH LOG:    /Users/steve/Documents/3SK/outputs/_Iris_Memory/Projects/Pitch_Log.md
REPORT DIR:   /Users/steve/Documents/3SK/outputs/04_Marketing_and_Sponsors/Pipeline_Status
NOTIFY: /Volumes/AI_Workspace/iris_studio/scripts/notify.sh

HARD RULES (read before doing anything):
- NEVER send an email, DM, or any external message, and NEVER instruct anyone/anything to send one. This routine and the sponsor-outreach-drafter it may dispatch are DRAFT-ONLY. Every send is Steve's, performed personally. Each Outreach draft carries a SEND GATE that must be met first — respect it; you only track and draft, you never trip the gate.
- NEVER fabricate a channel metric (subs, views, CPM). Quote numbers only from METRICS. If METRICS still says PRE-LAUNCH / no audience numbers, say so — do not invent reach to make a prospect look ready.
- This routine writes ONLY: one dated status report under REPORT DIR and your one daily-note line. It MAY dispatch `sponsor-outreach-drafter` (which writes its own draft under OUTREACH DIR). Do NOT edit the prospect list, existing drafts, the screening standard, metrics, or the pitch log.
- Do NOT delete or move any file.
- ALERT DISCIPLINE — silent by default. Fire the Telegram alert ONLY when Steve has an action: the SEND GATE just opened, a follow-up on a sent outreach is due, or a new draft is ready for his review. A quiet pipeline week (gate still closed, nothing due) raises no alert. The wrapper sends its own ✅; do not duplicate it.

PASS 1 — READ STATE:
  Read PROSPECTS (the ranked list + fit scores + contact paths), every file in OUTREACH DIR, METRICS, SCREENING, and PITCH LOG. Build a picture of: which prospects have a draft vs none; each draft's status (HOLD / ready / sent) and its SEND GATE conditions + prior-outreach-count/date.

PASS 2 — EVALUATE THE SEND GATE:
  Determine whether the outreach SEND GATE conditions are met NOW. The canonical gate (per the Outreach drafts, e.g. rocket-money) is: (a) first videos are LIVE on the channel, (b) 3skfinance.co is deployed with several live pages, and (c) the Impact publisher account is created + approved. Judge each condition from the vault state you can see (METRICS for live-video/subscriber state; the landing-page + Impact state from METRICS or the drafts' own notes). Do NOT assume the gate is open — if you cannot confirm a condition, treat it as not-yet-met and say which one is unconfirmed.
  - If the gate is CLOSED: the pipeline is in pre-send hold. You do NOT draft new outreach and you do NOT alert about follow-ups (nothing has been sent). You only note gate status in the report. The one exception worth an alert: if the gate just FLIPPED to open this week (a condition that was unmet is now met) — then alert Steve that outreach can begin.

PASS 3 — PROSPECT STATUS + FOLLOW-UPS (only meaningful once things are sent):
  For each prospect:
    • No draft + high fit (top of the ranked list) + gate OPEN → candidate for a fresh draft (PASS 4).
    • Draft exists, status HOLD, gate CLOSED → correctly parked; no action.
    • Draft exists, marked SENT (prior-outreach-count >= 1 with a send date) → compute days since last contact; if it exceeds a sensible follow-up window (default ~10–14 business days) with no reply logged → FOLLOW-UP DUE (flag for alert; do NOT send — Steve sends).
  Use only what the files say. If nothing has been sent yet (the current pre-launch reality), there are no follow-ups due.

PASS 4 — DRAFT THE NEXT OUTREACH (only if gate OPEN and a high-fit prospect has no draft):
  If and only if the SEND GATE is open AND the highest-fit prospect without a draft clears the SCREENING rubric: dispatch the `sponsor-outreach-drafter` subagent for that ONE prospect (give it the prospect name, archetype, contact path, fit notes from PROSPECTS, and the live numbers from METRICS). It writes a DRAFT under OUTREACH DIR with its own SEND GATE. Make clear in the dispatch: draft only, Steve sends. Do at most one new draft per run.
  If the gate is closed, SKIP this pass entirely.

PASS 5 — REPORT + ALERT:
  Write REPORT DIR/<today>_pipeline-status.md (create the dir) with frontmatter (date, type: sponsor-pipeline-status): the SEND GATE status (each condition met/unmet/unconfirmed), a per-prospect status line (draft? status? follow-up due?), and any draft you dispatched (with the drafter's return summary).
  IF Steve has an action (gate just opened / follow-up due / new draft ready for review):
    Fire ONE Telegram alert:
        /Volumes/AI_Workspace/iris_studio/scripts/notify.sh "🤝 Sponsor pipeline:
    • <gate opened — outreach can begin | follow-up due: <prospect>, last contact <date> | new draft ready for review: <prospect> (<path>)>
    ...
    Report: <report path>"
  IF the gate is closed and nothing is due (the normal pre-launch week): no alert.

PASS 6 — LOG (always, exactly one short line):
  Append to today's daily note /Users/steve/Documents/3SK/outputs/_Iris_Memory/Daily/<YYYY-MM-DD>.md under a section headed EXACTLY:
      ## 🤝 Sponsor-tracker (weekly Mon 07:00)
  ONE line: gate open/closed, # prospects with drafts, # follow-ups due, # new drafts this run, + report path. Create the daily note from 01_Operating_Docs/Templates/Daily_Note_Template.md (or a minimal stub) if missing. Do not touch any other agent's section.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## ⛳ Completion signal — REQUIRED LAST LINE (run_claude_job.sh reads this for Steve's Telegram alert)

After all work and logging, the VERY LAST line of your output MUST be exactly one of:
- `ROUTINE_COMPLETE` — the tracker ran (whether or not the gate is open or anything was drafted).
- `ROUTINE_INCOMPLETE: <one-line reason>` — you could not read the sponsor pipeline files at all.

Output nothing after that line.
